<P>
VEGAS POLICE HOLD S.D. MAN ON DRUG CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Diego man has been ordered held without bond on charges of conspiracy to 
manufacture methamphetamine. 
</P>
<P>
Timothy Dale Alexander was arrested by Drug Enforcement Administration agents 
here Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Green, chief of the U.S. attorney's Drug Task Force, told U.S. Magistrate 
Robert Johnson in a bail hearing Tuesday that Alexander was a sophisticated 
drug trafficker. Green said Alexander bragged to undercover agents that he 
would kill police if they tried to arrest him. 
</P>
<P>
