<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST CONFERENCE WOMEN'S TOURNAMENT; 
</P>
<P>
PACIFIC HANDS IRVINE 24TH LOSS IN ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The University of the Pacific women's basketball team defeated UC Irvine, 
71-51, Wednesday before only 121 in the first round of the Big West Conference 
tournament at Long Beach Arena. 
</P>
<P>
It was the Anteaters' 27th loss in 28 games and their 24th in a row. 
</P>
<P>
Both are school records. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine's only victory this season was a 59-57 win over Southern Utah State on 
Dec. 8. 
</P>
<P>
Center Julie Szukalski scored 19 points and guard Charmon Logan had 15 to lead 
Pacific (14-14), which meets Hawaii today at 3 p.m. Kathy Lizarraga and Jenny 
Lee, both guards, had 12 each to lead UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters had 35 turnovers and shot 35.2% from the field. 
</P>
<P>
San Jose State 81, San Diego State 59 -- Hulett Brooks had 22 points, making 
nine of 12 shots from the field, to lead San Jose State. Lora Alexander added 
20 points and 16 rebounds for the Spartans. 
</P>
<P>
San Jose (5-23) advances to play top-seeded Nevada Las Vegas at 7 tonight. 
</P>
<P>
The Spartans led only 34-27 at halftime, but gradually pulled away in the 
second half. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State (7-23) was led by Julie Evans, who had 16 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
