<TEXT>
<P>
Laurie Cottrell, assistant to the Brea city manager for the past three years, 
has been named Pasadena's new director of communications. 
</P>
<P>
She will oversee the city's public information and telecommunications programs. 
A former television newscaster in Michigan, Cottrell, 34, held similar jobs 
with the cities of Grand Rapids, Mich., and Santa Ana. She begins her $62,000 
Pasadena job April 2, replacing Christine Sanchez, who announced her 
resignation in January. 
</P>
