<P>
SAN JOSE; 
</P>
<P>
CSU OFFICIALS HIT FOR BUYING CARS SECRETLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
California State University officials, criticized for quietly giving themselves 
fat raises last year, now are under fire for secretly buying themselves cars 
with state funds. 
</P>
<P>
The university bought six Ford Taurus automobiles for vice chancellors, 
apparently without public discussion, the San Jose Mercury News reported. The 
cars cost a total of $99,998.70, just $1.30 below the threshold for an 
automatic review by the state Department of Finance. A CSU budget officer said 
the price was a coincidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
