<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 AREA TEAMS PLAY TONIGHT IN SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four area teams play tonight at 7:30 in the Southern regional semifinals of the 
state high school basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Poly and Lynwood will play each other for the second time in six days. 
</P>
<P>
The Jackrabbits edged the Knights, 60-58, for the CIF Southern Section title 
last Saturday night. The game will be at Long Beach City College. 
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday night's quarterfinals, Poly, trailing by 10 points with 50 seconds 
left in regulation, beat Loyola, 78-72, in overtime. Lynwood, with Earnest 
Killum scoring 45 points, defeated National City Sweetwater, 82-79, in three 
overtimes. 
</P>
<P>
Artesia will play at home against El Camino of Oceanside. The Pioneers, with Ed 
O'Bannon scoring 30 points, reached the Division II semifinals by defeating 
Golden West of Visalia, 65-36. 
</P>
<P>
Brethren, in Division V, will play El Cajon Christian at Granite Hills High in 
El Cajon. The Warriors defeated Community Christian, 72-56, Tuesday night in 
Bakersfield. 
</P>
</TEXT>
