<P>
SP to Acquire Digital Signal: Southern Pacific Telecommunications, a subsidiary 
of Southern Pacific Transportation of San Francisco, has signed a definitive 
agreement to acquire the Southfield, Mich., company. 
</P>
<P>
Terms of the deal were not disclosed. SP provides optical-fiber communications 
between Houston and San Francisco and arranges for installation of similar 
systems for long-distance carriers and companies along its 15,000 miles of 
railroad. Digital Signal provides private-line service for long-distance 
carriers between 88 cities. 
</P>
