$2.2-Billion Plane Engine Order: Singapore Airlines has decided to fit the 30 
Boeing 747-400 and 20 McDonnell Douglas MD-11 aircraft it is buying with 
American-made Pratt &amp; Whitney engines worth about $2.2 billion, the company 
said. In a news release, the airline said it spent four months evaluating three 
engines, including the General Electric CF6-80c2BIF and the Rolls Royce 
RB211-524H, before deciding on the Pratt &amp; Whitney PW 4056 for the Boeing 
747-400. Pratt &amp; Whitney engines are made by United Technologies Corp. of 
Hartford, Conn. 
