<P>
Texas Thrift Sold to Perelman Firm: The federal Resolution Trust Corp. has 
decided to sell San Antonio Savings Assn. to Houston-based First Gibraltar 
Bank, possibly as early as Friday, according to published reports. San Antonio 
Savings was seized in March, 1989. First Gibraltar, formed from the merger of a 
group of thrifts acquired in 1988 by New York financier Ronald O. Perelman, is 
the largest savings and loan in Texas. 
