<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kristina Lindgren and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR: The Daughters of the American Revolution, now convening in Costa Mesa 
(N1), count some familiar names among their members: First Ladies Barbara Bush, 
Rosalynn Carter and Bess Truman. . . . And while some members, such as 
conservative activist Phyllis Schlafly, may fit the DAR stereotype, others from 
the entertainment community may not. . . . These include actresses Lillian Gish 
and Ginger Rogers, talk show host Tawny Little and Laguna Beach's Harriet 
Nelson. Kristina Lindgren and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
