<HEADLINE>
<P>
WANG SELLING INTECOM UNIT TO FRENCH FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Financially troubled Wang Laboratories Inc. will sell subsidiary InteCom Inc., 
a maker of communication switching systems, to the French electronics firm 
Matra S.A. for an undisclosed price. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds will further reduce the financially troubled computer company's debt 
and increase its cash, Wang officials said. 
</P>
<P>
"We continue to make steady and deliberate progress in our program to sell 
non-strategic assets to eliminate Wang's debt to its bank group," said Richard 
W. Miller, president and chief operating officer, in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
In mid-February, Wang's bank debt totaled $308 million, spokesman Ed Pignone 
said. On Feb. 26, the company agreed to sell its international lease financing 
operations. This sale will reduce bank debt to $93 million, Pignone said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
