<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: REWARD RISES TO $20,000 IN FATAL UCLA 
SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Officials at UCLA Medical Center have doubled the reward for information on 
last month's shooting that left one employee dead and another seriously 
injured. 
</P>
<P>
The center is now offering $20,000 for information leading to the arrest and 
conviction of the gunman who killed 22-year-old Diondra Picou on Feb. 19. 
</P>
<P>
Another hospital worker, Nora Arellano, 30, suffered multiple gunshot wounds 
and was in fair condition Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Homicide detective Andy Monsue said police have not received any calls on the 
case, but are pursuing several leads. "I think the key to the case lies in 
someone at the hospital and that's what we're trying to draw out," Monsue said. 
</P>
<P>
Anyone with information on the crime is asked to call Lt. Jim Kuehn of the UCLA 
Police at (213) 825-1793 or the LAPD at (213) 312-8401, or 312-8441 in the 
evenings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
