<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: OFF-DUTY OFFICER SHOOTS TRANSIENT TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An off-duty Culver City police officer shot and killed a transient who 
allegedly was threatening him with a belt early Wednesday in Hollywood, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred shortly before 2 a.m. in an underground garage on 
Hollywood Boulevard at North Sycamore Avenue, said Los Angeles Police Lt. 
Joseph Garcia. 
</P>
<P>
The Culver City officer, a 12-year veteran who was not otherwise identified, 
was returning to his parked vehicle when the transient tried to assault him 
with a belt that had a "large buckle,", according to Garcia. The officer, 
"repeatedly tried to avoid the unprovoked attack," said Garcia, before he drew 
his gun and fired once, striking the transient in the upper torso. 
</P>
<P>
The wounded man was pronounced dead at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center. His name 
was withheld pending notification of relatives. The case will be investigated 
by LAPD detectives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
