<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
O.C. WOMAN HELD IN TRAFFIC DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 34-year-old Anaheim woman was arrested on suspicion of felony drunk driving 
Wednesday night after her car slammed into a father and daughter crossing a 
Stanton street, killing the man, sheriff's officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Nasario Romero Miranda, 57, of Stanton was pronounced dead at Midwood Hospital 
in Stanton. 
</P>
<P>
His daughter, Gloria Maria Romero, 24, also received several injuries, but a 
Sheriff's Department spokesman said she is in fair condition at Humana West 
Hospital in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Penney Patricia Bustamantez, 34, was in custody today after being arrested on 
suspicion of felony drunk driving. Bustamantez may face vehicular manslaughter 
charges, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's Lt. Harold Schaffroth said the incident occurred at 5:01 p.m. when 
Miranda and his daughter were walking in the marked crosswalk across Dale 
Street at Chanticleer Road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
