<TEXT>
<P>
Bobby McFerrin usually makes his own sound effects but on Sunday he will have 
the San Francisco Symphony to back him up. The Grammy-winning singer will 
conduct Beethoven's Symphony No. 7 and also will perform his "headTales," a 
composition for voice and cello, with the celebrated cellist Yo-Yo Ma. The 
program also features McFerrin's new 10-voice a cappella ensemble, Voicestra. 
</P>
