<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
NADIA, PANAIT SPLIT, FRIENDS SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN CITY, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nadia Comaneci's agent says she may have broken up with Constantin Panait, the 
married man who engineered her escape from Romania. 
</P>
<P>
The Olympic gymnast canceled her first U.S. appearance on the lecture circuit, 
apparently because she was upset over the breakup, said her agent, Bob Davis. 
</P>
<P>
She was to have given a speech Wednesday night at Nassau Community College. 
</P>
<P>
Davis said he has not spoken to Comaneci since she left for Tokyo more than a 
week ago with Panait, a roofer with a wife and four children in Florida. But 
people in Comaneci's entourage say the two broke up en route back from Japan, 
Davis said. 
</P>
<P>
Comaneci is staying with friends in Montreal, Davis said, where she won the 
first perfect 10s in Olympic gymnastics history in 1976. Panait is on the road. 
</P>
<P>
Comaneci said in a recent magazine interview that she and Panait had no plans 
to marry. She said last month that she intends to marry a 30-year-old fellow 
Romanian who is expected to enter the United States later this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
