NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
PAVAROTTI DIET TRIMS 80 POUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luciano Pavarotti says a diet to reduce his substantial girth has melted away 
80 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
When pressed at a news conference Wednesday, however, he refused to say how 
much he weighs. 
</P>
<P>
"I have lost 80 pounds and so I am 80 pounds less than I was," Pavarotti said 
with a broad smile. Asked how he did it, Pavarotti replied: "Very simple. I 
don't take alcohol, sugar or fat. Just 1,800 calories a day. It's brilliant." 
</P>
<P>
To laughter, he said: "Tonight, I will have a beautiful piece of salmon with 
vegetables, a piece of bread, strawberries, mineral water and lemon and coffee. 
What do you want more?" 
</P>
<P>
The 54-year-old Italian tenor was in London for his first appearance in nearly 
six years at the Royal Opera House, Covent Garden. 
</P>
</TEXT>
