<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
1994 WINTER OLYMPICS IN DOUBT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LILLEHAMMER, Norway 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Gerhard Heiberg of the Lillehammer Olympic Organizing Committee said 
the 1994 Winter Games may have to be dropped unless the Norwegian Parliament 
makes firm decisions about investments and arenas by early April, a newspaper 
reported today. 
</P>
<P>
Lillehammer was awarded the Games by the International Olympic Committee more 
than two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
Parliament has not yet provided the financial guarantees the organizing 
committee needs to start construction work and other preparations. 
</P>
<P>
The Lillehammer Tilskuer quoted Heiberg as telling local businessmen and 
investors, "By April 5 the location of arenas, the cost and investment 
guidelines and the whole organization model must be decided by Parliament. If 
not, or if major Olympic decisions are delayed until next fall, the entire 
arrangement is at risk and we should consider dropping the Games." 
</P>
</TEXT>
