<P>
PATHE AT A GLANCE 
</P>
<P>
NET INCOME/LOSS in millions of dollars (fiscal year ended Dec. 31) 
</P>
<P>
(9 mos. ended Sept.30: $54.6-million loss) 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday close (NYSE): $4.75, up 50 cents 
</P>
<P>
52-week range: $2.625-$5.00 
</P>
<P>
Shareholders: 1,900 
</P>
<P>
Common stock: 18.37 million (Florio Fiorini and Giancarlo Parretti and their 
affiliates own 87%. Yoram Globus holds 5%). 
</P>
<P>
Total assets: $611.9 million (Sept. 30, 1989) 
</P>
<P>
Current titles: "The Russia House," with Sean Connery and Michelle Pfeiffer; 
"Quigley Down Under," with Tom Selleck; "The Fires Within," with Greta Scaachi 
and Jimmy Smits; "Not Without My Daughter," with Sally Field; "Dinosaurs," with 
Gene Hackman and Mikhail Baryshnikov; "Life Stinks," with Mel Brooks 
</P>
<P>
Movie theaters: 1,000 screens in five European countries 
</P>
<P>
Film library: 1,200 titles 
</P>
<P>
Headquarters: Beverly Hills 
</P>
<P>
Chief executive: Giancarlo Parretti 
</P>
<P>
Sources: Pathe Communications, Standard &amp; Poor's, Reuters 
</P>
